ww.mexicanos.co/2010/hoja-de-datos-para-sb-1070/ Hoja de resumen para la S.B. 1070])\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170616130123/https://www.supremecourt.gov/oral_arguments/argument_transcripts/11-182.pdf ''Arizona, et al. v. United States'' U.S. Supreme Court oral arguments transcript] and [https://www.supremecourt.gov/oral_arguments/argument_audio_detail.aspx?argument=11-182 audio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20131218121656/http://www.castlibrary.com/audio_books/united-states-supreme-court-arizona-vs-united-states Arizona v. United States Audio Book] Bookmarkable m4b audio book of the arguments in ''Arizona v. United States''\n{{Immigration to the United States}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Arizona Sb1070}}\n[[Category:Arizona statutes]]\n[[Category:United States immigration law]]\n[[Category:2010 in American law]]\n[[Category:2010 in Arizona]]\n[[Category:Race and law in the United States]]\n[[Category:Illegal immigration to the United States]]\n[[Category:Immigration legislation]]\n[[Category:Forced migrations in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Aperson0", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arizona_SB_1070"}
{"title_page": "Ushimado, Okayama", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n\n[[File:Setouchi Ushimado Port04n3200.jpg|thumb|Ushimado Port]]\n\n{{nihongo|'''Ushimado'''|\u725b\u7a93\u753a|Ushimado-ch\u014d}} was a [[List of towns in Japan|town]] located in [[Oku District, Okayama|Oku District]], [[Okayama Prefecture]], [[Japan]].\n\nAs of 2003, the town had an estimated [[population]] of 7,545 and a [[population density|density]] of 274.36 persons per km\u00b2. The total area was 27.50&nbsp;km\u00b2.\n\nOn November 1, 2004, Ushimado, along with the towns of [[Oku, Okayama|Oku]] and [[Osafune, Okayama|Osafune]] (all from [[Oku District, Okayama|Oku District]]), was merged to create the city of [[Setouchi, Okayama|Setouchi]].\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Commons category|Ushimado}}\n\n[[Category:Dissolved municipalities of Okayama Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2004]]\n[[Category:2004 disestablishments in Japan]]\n{{Okayama-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n\n[[File:Setouchi Ushimado Port04n3200.jpg|thumb|Ushimado Port]]\n\n{{nihongo|'''Ushimado'''|\u725b\u7a93\u753a|Ushimado-ch\u014d}} was a [[List of towns in Japan|town]] located in [[Oku District, Okayama|Oku District]], [[Okayama Prefecture]], [[Japan]].\n\nAs of 2003, the town had an estimated [[population]] of 7,545 and a [[population density|density]] of 274.36 persons per km\u00b2. The total area was 27.50&nbsp;km\u00b2.\n\nOn November 1, 2004, Ushimado, along with the towns of [[Oku, Okayama|Oku]] and [[Osafune, Okayama|Osafune]] (all from [[Oku District, Okayama|Oku District]]), was merged to create the city of [[Setouchi, Okayama|Setouchi]].\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Commons category|Ushimado}}\n\n[[Category:Dissolved municipalities of Okayama Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2004]]\n[[Category:2004 disestablishments in Japan]]\n{{Okayama-geo-stub}}\n[[Category:2000s disestablishments in Japan]]\n", "name_user"