ar Playhouse''\n|\n| \"The Tenth Planet\"<ref name=\"Goldin Hollywood Star\"/><ref name=\"Archive Hollywood Star\"/>\n|-\n| September 14, 1952\n| ''Theatre Guild On the Air''\n|\n| \"The Wisteria Tree\"<ref name=\"Goldin Theatre Guild\"/>\n|-\n| October 12, 1952\n| ''Hallmark Playhouse''\n|\n| \"Young Mr. Disraeli\"<ref name=\"Goldin Hallmark\"/>\n|-\n| December 22, 1952\n| ''Suspense''\n|\n| \"Arctic Rescue\"<ref name=\"Goldin Suspense\"/><ref name=\"Archive Suspense Singles\"/><ref>{{cite news| last1=Kirby| first1=Walter| title=Better Radio Programs for the Week| url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/2578496/the_decatur_daily_review/| newspaper=The Decatur Daily Review| date=December 21, 1952| page=44| via=Newspapers.com| accessdate=June 8, 2015}} {{Open access}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 28, 1952\n| ''Hallmark Playhouse''\n|\n| \"A Man Called Peter\"<ref name=\"Goldin Hallmark\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/details/HallmarkPlayhouse |title=Hallmark Playhouse |publisher=Internet Archive |accessdate=2015-11-07}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 11, 1953\n| ''Theatre Guild On the Air''\n|\n| \"Jane\"<ref name=\"Goldin Theatre Guild\"/>\n|-\n| January 14, 1953\n| ''Philip Morris Playhouse on Broadway''\n|\n| \"[[Hold Back the Dawn]]\"<ref name=\"Philip Morris Digital Deli\"/><ref name=ddr1>{{cite news| last1=Kirby| first1=Walter| title=Better Radio Programs for the Week| url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/2648547/the_decatur_daily_review/| newspaper=The Decatur Daily Review| date=January 11, 1953| page=42| via=Newspapers.com| accessdate=June 19, 2015}} {{Open access}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 18, 1953\n| ''Theatre Guild on the Air''\n|\n| \"Trial by Forgery\"<ref name=\"Theatre Guild Digital Deli\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitaldeliftp.com/DigitalDeliToo/dd2jb-Theatre-Guild-On-The-Air.html |title=Theatre Guild On the Air  |publisher=The Digital Deli Too |accessdate=2015-11-06}}</ref><ref name=ddr1/>\n|-\n| January 26, 1953\n| ''Lux Radio Theatre''\n| David Lawrence\n| \"