{"title_page": "Tsukui, Kanagawa", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=July 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox city Japan\n| name             = Tsukui\n| native_name      = \u6d25\u4e45\u4e95\u753a\n| settlement_type  = Former municipality\n| image_skyline    = \n| image_caption    = \n| image_map        = Map kanagawa tsukui town p01-01.png\n| coordinates      = {{coord|35.5838|N|139.2584|E|region:JP|display=inline,title}}\n| region           = [[Kant\u014d region|Kant\u014d]]\n| prefecture       = [[Kanagawa Prefecture]]\n| district         = [[Tsukui District, Kanagawa|Tsukui]]\n| merged           = March 11, 2007\n| merged_into      = [[Sagamihara, Kanagawa|Sagamihara]]\n| area_km2         = 122.04\n| population       = 28,551\n| population_as_of = March 1, 2006\n| density_km2      = 233.9\n| tree             = [[Maple]]\n| flower           = [[Rhododendron]]\n| bird             = [[Japanese bush-warbler]]\n| website          = \n| footnotes        = \n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''Tsukui'''|\u6d25\u4e45\u4e95\u753a|Tsukui-machi}} was a [[List of towns of Japan|town]] located in [[Tsukui District, Kanagawa|Tsukui District]], [[Kanagawa Prefecture]], [[Japan]].\n\nAs of March 1, 2006, final population data before the amalgamation, the town had an estimated [[population]] of 28,551 and a [[population density|density]] of 233.9 persons per km<sup>2</sup>. The total area was 122.04&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.\n\nOn March 20, 2006, Tsukui, along with the town of [[Sagamiko, Kanagawa|Sagamiko]] (also from [[Tsukui District, Kanagawa|Tsukui District]]), [[Municipal mergers and dissolutions in Japan|was merged]] into the expanded city of [[Sagamihara, Kanagawa|Sagamihara]], and thus no longer exists as an independent [[Municipalities of Japan|municipality]]. It is now part of [[Midori-ku, Sagamihara]].\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Dissolved municipalities of Kanagawa Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2006]]\n[[Category:2006 disestablishments in Japan]]\n{{Kanagawa-geo-stu